In a speech at the United States Holocaust Memorial Museum, Lieutenant General H.R. McMaster discussed the ongoing Syrian civil war and the atrocities committed by the Assad regime and ISIS. He emphasized the importance of remembrance and action, stating that the United States is documenting atrocities, fighting alongside partners to defeat terrorist organizations, providing humanitarian aid to victims, and working to hold Assad accountable for his use of chemical weapons. McMaster also called for accountability for the sponsors of the Assad regime, namely Iran and Russia, and urged all nations to impose political and economic consequences on them. He concluded by highlighting the importance of remembering the victims of both the Holocaust and the Syrian civil war and the need for collective responsibility in preventing genocide and mass atrocities.